data.description: Absolutely stunning custom ranch professionally designed with exceptional attention to detail. Inspired by the Mediterranean style popular in Florida in the 1920's, this meticulous hacienda style home is full of exquisite details. With ten acres of land and nestled among grandfather oaks, the entrance is unassuming and private. Wind your way to the house and detached garage/barn, complete with 3 full garage bays. The side entry to the garage allows extra parking and easy turn around.   As you enter the home, take in the the fine, old world finishes, imported tile, cypress ceiling, and imported, antique lighting. The great room anchors the home and with soaring 20' ceilings it is a focal point. The custom cabinetry and library shelving are a true blend of form and function. The dining area and stunning chandelier open to the outdoor portico with a bank of French doors.   The heart of this home is the stunning, chef's kitchen with Wolf ovens and cooktop, SubZero Refrigerator, 2 Asko dishwashers, dual sinks with Rohl fixtures. Somewhat of a celebrity, this kitchen has hosted the Wolf chef as a tribute to the designers. The cabinetry is finely crafted and custom designed to accent the imported marble. The coffered ceiling features hand painted stenciled beams. The 6' by 9' island is perfect for entertaining, sipping espresso or watching the chef in your family. Located off the kitchen, the mud room with matching cabinetry, features an antique European baby sink, also perfect for dog washing.    This home also has dual master suites, each with its own en-suite bath and upgraded closets. Don't miss the custom tile, built-in cabinets, walk-in shower, and air tub.   Adjacent the kitchen is a private guest suite with hall bath perfect for guests. Peek in the shower to see the 'cracked' tile floor.  Go upstairs and take in the dual offices in the loft. The cypress floors are warm and hearty. Use this area for office space, a gallery, yoga studio, or as a retreat, you decide.    As you walk outside, linger on the open air porch and gaze toward the reflecting pool connecting the home with the barn. The serene surroundings are peaceful and beautiful. Host a large party or enjoy a fire in the tiled fireplace, this is outdoor living at its best.    The barn is an equestrian's dream. With 5 large stalls, a tack room, kitchen/feed room with toilet area. The portico is a fully functional for tacking up and as a wash rack, or use as an outdoor shower for the pool. With both hot and cold water and a storage cabinet, this area is also perfect for entertaining.   The barn has a separate septic system and metal roof. Plenty of room to convert this to additional living space or a guest cottage. The barn and garage share the same craftsman stucco finish and truly complement the house. Flagstone walkways surround the home and showcase the master gardener's work.    There is a separate pole barn with electric suitable as a run in shelter, trailer storage, boat storage or additional stalls. Located on the  western side of the property there is also a 50' nature buffer for privacy. At the rear of the property, there is a 25' access road if needed.   Located 52 miles from Orlando, 59 miles from Tampa, and 12 miles from the nearest FBO airport in Inverness this home is a jewel in waiting.  With so many curated and designed features, this home can only be fully appreciated with a private tour. Schedule today before this opportunity is gone.
